01:11:00.726 --> 01:11:04.296
In addition, we're also able to assign mutational processes to the branches of this

1209
01:11:04.306 --> 01:11:07.966
tree, and we notice that this patient had a high degree of APOBEC mutagenesis.

1210
01:11:09.306 --> 01:11:12.886
And then we can also compare the trees that we built with the PPMseq to

1211
01:11:12.926 --> 01:11:16.846
the full trees that we built with both the tissue and the cell-free DNA whole

1212
01:11:16.926 --> 01:11:20.686
exome. And we see there's higher concordance in these whole genome trees

1213
01:11:20.726 --> 01:11:24.696
compared to the whole exome trees from the only whole exome cell-free

1214
01:11:24.726 --> 01:11:28.706
DNA trees. In this case, we see these individual ESR1 clones

1215
01:11:28.766 --> 01:11:32.446
on both trees, which we didn't see in the whole

1216
01:11:32.486 --> 01:11:33.426
